cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep learning models and their limitations in maintaining performance on new test domains. Specifically, it focuses on image styles and proposes techniques to ignore them and focus on image contents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions adversarial learning, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions consistency learning, which is a technique in natural language processing, a sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with image blending, which is a technique in multimedia, a sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
